p: The concentration of humulene epoxide 2 (bicyclic sesquiterpenoid) was 1.3 to 3.2% in wild hemp, 0.4 to 2.3% in registered hemp cultivars, and 2.3 to 5.6% in the EO of the breeding lines ( Supplementary Tables S1â€“S3). Overall, the concentration of humulene epoxide 2 was statistically higher in the cvs. Bacalmas and Sequieni, and the lowest in cv. Spic ( Table 2). The concentration of this compound in the USA hemp strain EO was 0.47%. The concentration of this compound in the EO of wild hemp from Austria was <2.5% [ 15], while in the EO of spontaneous hemp from Hungary, it was 1.2, 1.1, and 0.6% in the leaves, male, and female flowers, respectively [ 18].
